text.tspan: 1. Divide into teams. Anyone who played Go Solo is on their own team
2. Starting with any team that played Go Solo (breaking ties with commitment, then
Beats-Melody-Front), claim and discard a song that a player on that team has a
credit on. for every square of music that song has, move up 1 on the Crowd track
3. Team members pool their unspent committment. For every 2 unspent committment,
move up 1 on the Crowd track
Teamed-up players add their crowd score and put their score markers at that
position on the Crowd track. They move them together
4. The team furthest along the Crowd track WINS!
Winning players get to keep their character sheets for the next game.
The other (non-winning) players must retire their character sheet, and make brand
new characters at the start of the next game
